== 4...Qe7 · Kholmov gambit ==
Black allow White to take their knight but prepares to pin White's knight. 

White will be ahead a pawn if he simply accepts the knight, so [[/5. Qxe4|'''5. Qxe4''']] is almost universally played. This pins White's knight to their queen, so Black can recover the piece for the cost of the d-pawn.  5...d6 6. d4 dxe5 7. dxe5 Nc6{{Chess/not|+}} and Black has partial compensation. White then usually gives back the pawn: if they cling onto it they can find themselves trapped. 

=== History ===

The gambit is named for Russian grandmaster [[wikipedia:Ratmir Kholmov|Ratmir Kholmov]] (1925―2006), though he is not known to have played it as Black. The misunderstanding may come from a misattribution of the game Kholmov v Belousov, 1974.<ref>[https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1578359 Kholmov v Belousov, 1974 - Chessgames.com]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ratmir Kholmov |url=https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessplayer?pid=15362 |date=2023-07-04 |website=Chessgames.com}}</ref>

